data.name: JVM
data.description: View of key metrics relating to the health and performance of Java Virtual machine running on AWS EC2 instance.

markdown.markdownText:
**JVM**

The Java Virtual Machine (JVM)is the runtime environment that enables Java applications to execute. JVMs are widely used across a range of applications, from web services to enterprise software, making it essential to monitor their performance and resource usage to ensure smooth operations. Proper JVM monitoring helps in identifying performance bottlenecks, optimizing resource utilization, and preventing potential issues that can impact application stability and responsiveness.

This dashboard is part of the out-of-box AWS extension and provides visibility to and alerting on key performance metrics.

**Use Cases Covered**

* JVM CPU utilisation
* JVM CPU time in seconds
* Heap Memory used/committed/max
* Non Heap Memory used/committed/max
* Number of executing thread by JVM thread daemon/State
    JVM garbage Collection Duration
* JVM Memory
* JVM Classes Loaded/Unloaded Count
    **More about performance monitoring of JVM workload on Amazon EC2** [ here](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudWatch/latest/monitoring/Solution-JVM-On-EC2.html)
